HEADWORD: Lucernaria
<hw>Lu`cer*na"ri*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL., fr.
L. <ets>lucerna</ets> a lamp.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of
acalephs, having a bell-shaped body with eight groups of short tentacles
around the margin. It attaches itself by a sucker at the base of the
pedicel.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

